President Biden and Prime Minister Trudeau of Canada held a meeting at the Los Angeles Convention Center. President Biden expressed his gratitude for the friendship between the two countries and emphasized the importance of the upcoming open hearings on the January 6th Capitol attack. He called it a clear violation of the Constitution and stated that those involved must be held accountable. The leaders discussed their upcoming engagements at the G7 and NATO conferences, as well as their shared vision for a democratic and prosperous hemisphere. Prime Minister Trudeau highlighted the deep friendship between Canada and the United States and the importance of supporting each other and promoting democracy globally. They also discussed their collaboration on issues such as Ukraine and climate change, and the need to create prosperity and good jobs in the Americas. The meeting concluded with brief remarks from both leaders.